messages.content: What is the purpose of the 'ControlNet Selector' node in suplex_comfy_nodes?
The 'ControlNet Selector' node allows you to select from all of your ControlNet models without forcing it to load them, making it great for passing to other nodes.
How does the 'Load Optional ControlNet Model' node differ from the original 'Load ControlNet Model' node in comfy core?

The 'Load Optional ControlNet Model' node is a fork of the original 'Load ControlNet Model' node. Instead of auto-assigning a ControlNet load and forcefully loading it, it has an extra None value that can be used to trigger it to no longer load anything.
What is the function of the 'Diffusers Selector' node in suplex_comfy_nodes?
The 'Diffusers Selector' node allows you to select from all of your Diffusers formatted models without forcing it to load them, making it great for passing to other nodes.
What does the 'Save Image JPG No Meta' node do?
The 'Save Image JPG No Meta' node saves a JPG image without metadata, with optional quality settings.
How does the 'Multi Input Variable Rewrite' node work?
The 'Multi Input Variable Rewrite' node allows using inputs as variables to rewrite a string.
Is the 'Load Optional ControlNet Model' node a part of the original ComfyUI core?
No, the 'Load Optional ControlNet Model' node is a fork of the original 'Load ControlNet Model' node from comfy core, and is included in suplex_comfy_nodes.
What types of models can be selected using the 'Diffusers Selector' node?
The 'Diffusers Selector' node allows you to select from all of your Diffusers formatted models.
